
Collection in Java
Definition

Collection is a framework in Java that provides classes and interfaces to store,
 manage, and manipulate groups of objects dynamically.

Unlike arrays, collections can grow and shrink automatically.

Simple Definition (Interview)

A Collection in Java is a framework used to store and manage multiple objects dynamically.

Why Collection is Needed?
Array Problems

❌ Fixed Size

int[] arr = new int[5];

Cannot increase size after creation.

❌ Stores only same data type.

❌ Insertion and deletion are difficult.

Collection Advantages

✅ Dynamic Size

✅ Easy Insertion

✅ Easy Deletion

✅ Searching Support

✅ Sorting Support

✅ Ready-made Data Structures

